# Single Source of Truth Implementation Plan

## 1. Field Definitions Object (Frontend)

Create a single `FIELD_DEFINITIONS` object that defines:
- Canvas API field names (these will be used as keys AND as headers)
- Field types (`text`, `number`, `datetime`, `boolean`)
- Editable status
- Render functions for read-only fields (e.g., `quiz_type`, `submission_types`, `author`, `message`)
- Column order

Structure:
```javascript
const FIELD_DEFINITIONS = {
  quizzes: [
    { key: 'id', type: 'number', editable: false },
    { key: 'title', type: 'text', editable: true },
    { key: 'quiz_type', type: 'text', editable: false, render: (val) => val || '-' },
    { key: 'due_at', type: 'datetime', editable: true },
    // ... etc
  ],
  // ... other tabs
}
```

## 2. Header Standardization

Change ALL table headers to use Canvas API keys directly:
- "Title" → `title`
- "Due Date" → `due_at`
- "Quiz Type" → `quiz_type`
- "Name" → `name` (for assignments)
- "Points" → `points_possible`
- "Posted At" → `posted_at`
- "Last Reply" → `last_reply_at`
- "Discussion Type" → `discussion_type`
- "Author" → `author`
- "Message" → `message`
- "Last Edited" → `updated_at`

## 3. Generic Display Function

Replace all individual display functions (`displayQuizzes`, `displayAssignments`, `displayDiscussions`, `displayAnnouncements`) with ONE generic function:

```javascript
function displayDataTable(tabName, items) {
  // Uses FIELD_DEFINITIONS[tabName] to:
  // - Generate table headers dynamically
  // - Generate table rows dynamically
  // - Initialize editable cells
  // - Handle empty states
}
```

Benefits:
- Removes ~200 lines of duplicated code
- Single place to modify table rendering logic
- Consistent behavior across all tabs

## 4. Helper Functions for Repeated Patterns

Create helper functions for:

a) `initializeTableState(tabName, items)` - Common setup code:
- Initialize `selectedItems[tabName]`
- Update count badge
- Clear tbody
- Reset select-all checkbox
- Handle empty state

b) `createTableRow(tabName, item, itemId, isChecked, fieldDefinitions)` - Row creation:
- Generate checkbox cell
- Generate cells for each field (editable or read-only)
- Apply render functions for read-only fields
- Return row element

c) `initializeEditableCells(row, tabName, itemId, item, fieldDefinitions)` - Cell initialization:
- Find all editable cells in row
- Call `makeCellEditable` and `displayCellValue` for each
- Reduces ~10 lines per display function to 1 function call

## 5. Dynamic Header Generation

Generate table headers from `FIELD_DEFINITIONS` instead of hardcoding in HTML:
- Remove hardcoded `<thead>` sections
- Generate headers on page load or when tab is first displayed
- Use Canvas API keys as header text

## 6. Common Code Consolidation

a) Date handling (already centralized - keep as is):
- `formatDateForDisplay()` ✓
- `formatDateForInput()` ✓
- `formatDateForAPI()` ✓

b) Cell editing logic (already centralized - keep as is):
- `makeCellEditable()` ✓
- `displayCellValue()` ✓

c) Sync logic:
- Keep quiz `due_at` routing to assignment endpoint (special case handling)
- Use `FIELD_DEFINITIONS` to determine editable fields for validation

## 7. Render Functions for Complex Fields

Define render functions in `FIELD_DEFINITIONS` for:
- `quiz_type`: Display as-is
- `submission_types`: Join array with commas
- `author`: Extract `display_name` or `name` from object
- `message`: Strip HTML tags, truncate to 100 chars
- `last_reply_at`: Format as date
- `discussion_type`: Display as-is
- `question_count`: Display number or 0

## 8. Implementation Order

1. Create `FIELD_DEFINITIONS` object with all field definitions
2. Update HTML headers to use Canvas API keys (or generate dynamically)
3. Create `displayDataTable()` generic function
4. Create helper functions (`initializeTableState`, `createTableRow`, `initializeEditableCells`)
5. Replace individual display functions with calls to `displayDataTable()`
6. Test each tab to ensure functionality is preserved
7. Remove old display functions

## 9. Code Reduction Estimate

- Current: ~400 lines across 4 display functions
- After: ~150 lines (generic function + helpers)
- Savings: ~250 lines

## 10. Special Cases to Preserve

- Quiz `due_at` routing to assignment endpoint (keep in sync logic)
- Students tab (different structure, keep separate)
- Pages tab (uses `url` as ID, may need special handling)
- Modules tab (different structure, may need special handling)
- Accommodations tab (different structure, keep separate)

## 11. Benefits

- Single source of truth for field definitions
- Headers match Canvas API keys exactly
- Easier to add new fields (just update FIELD_DEFINITIONS)
- Consistent behavior across all tabs
- Less code to maintain
- Easier debugging (one place to check)

## 12. Potential Risks

- Generic function may need special-case handling for some tabs
- Need to ensure render functions handle all edge cases
- Must preserve existing functionality (quiz due_at routing, etc.)


